  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2006-05-10",
    "date": "2006-05-16T21:28:01Z",
    "text": "Nurse Loan Forgiveness Act of 2006 - Amends the Higher Education Act of 1965 (HEA) to include, under HEA student loan forgiveness and cancellation programs, nurses who serve at least one calendar year in an approved health care facility or setting.\n\nLimits the maximum amount of such loan repayment by the Secretary of Education to not more than $2,000 after the first year of such a nurse's employment, with incremental increases after the second through fourth years, up to $5,000 after the fifth year of such employment."
  },
